<p class="lead">Selling on Amazon is a bit like renting a stall in someone else's mall — a mall that can decide to open its own competing stall right next to yours and undercut you on price. The fees are layered, the policies are complex, and the playing field tilts toward Amazon's own products more every year. If you're a seller looking for platforms that actually put you first, here are six Amazon Marketplace alternatives worth your attention in 2025.</p>

